\begin_layout Subsection*
2.
 The Type System Hierarchy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Scala has a unified type system.
 All types descend from a single root,
 
\family typewriter
Any
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
AnyVal
\series default
:
 Primitive-like types (
\family typewriter
Int
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Double
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Boolean
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Unit
\family default
).
 These are often optimized into JVM primitives.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
AnyRef
\series default
:
 All reference types (equivalent to 
\family typewriter
java.lang.Object
\family default
).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Nothing
\series default
:
 The "bottom type." It is a subtype of everything.
 A method that throws an exception or loops infinitely returns 
\family typewriter
Nothing
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Null
\series default
:
 A subtype of all 
\family typewriter
AnyRef 
\family default
types.
 It exists for Java interoperability,
 but its use is discouraged in idiomatic Scala in favor of 
\family typewriter
Option
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
3.
 Definitions and Variables
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Scala distinguishes between immutable and mutable storage at the keyword level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
val 
\family default
(
\series bold
Value
\series default
):
 Immutable reference.
 Once assigned,
 it cannot be changed.
 Equivalent to 
\family typewriter
final 
\family default
in Java or a constant in Ruby.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
var 
\family default
(
\series bold
Variable
\series default
):
 Mutable reference.
 Use is generally discouraged in functional Scala.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
def 
\family default
(
\series bold
Method
\series default
):
 Evaluated on every call.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
lazy val
\family default
:
 Evaluated only once,
 the first time it is accessed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
4.
 Expressions and Control Flow
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Scala,
 
\series bold
everything is an expression
\series default
.
 Unlike Ruby or Java,
 there are no "statements" that don't return a value.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
If/Else
\series default
:
 Returns a value.
 
\family typewriter
val result = if (x > 0) "pos" else "neg"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
For-Comprehensions
\series default
:
 More than a loop;
 it is syntactic sugar for 
\family typewriter
flatMap
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
map
\family default
,
 and 
\family typewriter
