 The "Safety Net"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Use Case:

\series default
 When you are calling "dirty" code (usually Java libraries) that might throw a runtime exception.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
The Logic
\series default
:
 It has two subclasses:
 
\family typewriter
Success(value)
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
Failure(exception)
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
When to use it:

\series default
 Parsing a string to an integer,
 reading a file,
 or any operation where a traditional JVM exception is likely.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
The Benefit
\series default
:
 It "catches" the exception and turns it into a value you can pass around.
\end_layout

