3.
 Either[L,
 R] —
 The "Business Logic" Type
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Use Case
\series default
:
 When an operation can fail,
 and you need to provide a specific reason for that failure (the "Left" value).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
The Logic
\series default
:
 By convention,
 
\series bold
Right 
\series default
is "Right" (Success),
 and 
\series bold
Left 
\series default
is for errors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
When to use it
\series default
:
 Domain logic.
 For example,
 
\series bold
sttp 
